Kubernetes:
kubectl get namespace =it will list the all name spaces
kubectl get pods -n namespace =it will list all the pods in the name spaces
kubectl delete pod podname -n namespace = it will restart the pod 
kubectl logs -f podname -n namespace = it will list the pod log details to check errors
kubectl scale --replicas=0 deployment deploymentname -n namespace =it will scale down pod to 0 
kubectl scale --replicas=1 deployment deploymentname -n namespace =it will scale up pod to 1 to 1000

docker:
docker images  =it will list all the images 
docker ps = it will list all the docker running container
docker ps -a = it will list all the running and stopped container details
docker rmi -f image id =it will remove the docker images 
docker start container id = it will strt the container 
docker stop container id = it will stop the container
docker rm container id = it will remove the container
docker exec -it container id bash =it will go inside the container

